Foot-and-mouth disease, Mongolia
--------------------------------
Information received on 9 Jul 2013 from Dr Baatar Togoonyam, Deputy Director and Chief Veterinary Officer, Veterinary and Animal Breeding Agency, Ministry for Industry and Agriculture, Ulaanbaatar, Mongolia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 4 Jul 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 5 Jul 2013
Report date: 8 Jul 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 9 Jul 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 5 Jan 2011
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Sar Bastay, Sagsai soum, Bayan-Ulgii
Date of start of the outbreak: 4 Jul 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 417 / 14 / 0 / 14 / 0
Goats / 280 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 614 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 2: Khar nuur, 6 bag, Ulaankhus soum, Bayan-Ulgii
Date of start of the outbreak: 6 Jul 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / not available / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 417 / 15 / 0 / 15 / 0
Goats / 280 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 614 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine, movement control inside the country, screening, disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), dipping/spraying, no vaccination, no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: State Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory)
